description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Dietitian&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are excited to be able to recruit to this new dietetic post which is part of wider developments to the CAMHS Eating Disorders Team which delivers to the population of Leicester, Leicestershire and Rutland (LLR).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post offers the opportunity for an enthusiastic and self-motivated Band 6 Dietitian to deliver and develop this new service. You will need to &lt;/span&gt;have&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working with children and adolescents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sound dietetic experience of managing a range of clinical conditions using a behaviour change approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing your own dietetic caseload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As well as you need to work with the MDT to develop their knowledge on nutrition and hydration issues and lead on service developments that are linked to eating and drinking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be based with the CAMHS Eating Disorders team and will have the support of the team managers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leicester Nutrition and Dietetic Service, which has a team of approximately 80 staff, working in primary care, mental health, public health and home enteral nutrition is made up of dietitians, community nutritionists, dietetic support workers and support team staff covering the population of LLR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to the nature of the work a car driver is essential&lt;/strong&gt;. Applicants must hold a full UK driving licence and have access to a car during working hours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a registered dietitian who has:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Relevant band 5/6 experience with good leadership,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Communication and team working skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;And can also work independently.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service is committed to CPD and personal development and we have good clinical supervision models and in-house CPD in place to support you. The service is involved in the pre-registration placements for student dietitians undertaking A, B and C placements, to which the post-holder will contribute.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base: &lt;/strong&gt;Mawson House – CAMHS Eating Disorders Team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interested? &lt;/strong&gt;Contact for more information:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Alison.Eivors@leicspart.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or 0116 2950310&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Alison.Scott@lnds.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or 0116 2227144 / 07585 991883&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
